    {
        "url": "/quotes/eric_maskin_726491",
        "quote": "If I buy a car, I use the car, you don't, and the market for cars works pretty well. But there are many other sorts of goods, often very important goods, which are not provided well through the market. Often, these go under the heading of public goods.",
