    {
        "url": "/quotes/eric_maskin_726484",
        "quote": "When a bank calls in a loan, it obviously hurts the customer in question. But it also adversely affects other banks that have lent to this borrower. They are now less likely to be repaid and so can't as readily lend to their own customers.",
